cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL 

This paper deals with convolutional neural networks and their architecture design for image classification benchmarks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also investigates the assumption of monotonously increasing feature-counts with higher layers, which falls under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the use of a parametrized framework and evaluation on image classification benchmarks suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper's focus on image classification could also place it under the sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language).
